<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77c50c33-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s460m–7"><num value="460m–7">§ 460m–7.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are hereby authorized to be appropriated such sums (but not more than $10,804,000 for the acquisition of lands or interests in lands) as are necessary to carry out the purposes of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id77c50c34-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/88/492/s8">Pub. L. 88–492, § 8</ref>, <date date="1964-08-27">Aug. 27, 1964</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/78/610">78 Stat. 610</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/92/272/tI/s101/7">Pub. L. 92–272, title I, § 101(7)</ref>, <date date="1972-04-11">Apr. 11, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/120">86 Stat. 120</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id77c50c35-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id77c50c36-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id77c50c37-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1972—<ref href="/us/pl/92/272">Pub. L. 92–272</ref> increased maximum amount authorized to be appropriated for acquisition of lands or interests in lands from not more than $7,000,000 to not more than $10,804,000.</p>
</note>
</notes>
